+# Business and Enterprise Account Plan
+
+## Status
+
+This document is for future planning only.
+
+The first public launch remains simple:
+
+```txt
+Free only
+18+ only
+No real ads
+No real AI
+No public Pro launch
+No public Business launch
+No wallet
+No payouts
+No money trades
+No Stripe
+No Airwallex
+Service / skill / need / offer exchange only
+```
+
+Business and Enterprise accounts must stay hidden until a later explicit launch decision.
+
+## Current repo foundation
+
+The current repo already contains hidden groundwork that can support Business accounts later:
+
+```txt
+BusinessProfile
+BusinessProfileMember
+MoneyProviderAccount.businessProfileId
+Need.businessProfileId
+Offer.businessProfileId
+Trade.businessProfileId
+InventoryTemplate.businessProfileId
+InventoryTemplate.sourceType = hellowhen | business | brand | partner
+```
+
+The current environment flags also keep Business accounts hidden:
+
+```txt
+BUSINESS_ACCOUNTS_VISIBLE=false
+NEXT_PUBLIC_BUSINESS_ACCOUNTS_VISIBLE=false
+EXPO_PUBLIC_BUSINESS_ACCOUNTS_VISIBLE=false
+```
+
+The existing Business API is useful as a skeleton, but it is not ready for public use. It currently covers basic owned business profiles, member visibility, review requests, provider-account hooks, and admin status changes. It does not yet provide a safe full product flow for team invitations, business-owned content creation, sponsored placements, campaigns, budgets, or public discovery.
+
+## Product definition
+
+Business accounts are verified organization accounts.
+
+They are separate from individual Free and individual Pro accounts.
+
+Business accounts are for:
+
+```txt
+companies
+brands
+agencies
+enterprise partners
+organizations that want to publish reviewed opportunities, sponsored Needs/Offers, or library items
+```
+
+Business accounts should not be treated as normal person-to-person trading accounts. A Business may create opportunities that individual users can discover and respond to, but Business users should not replace the core individual marketplace.
+
+## Account type boundaries
+
+Keep these layers separate:
+
+| Layer | Purpose | Includes later | Must not include at first |
+| --- | --- | --- | --- |
+| Individual Free | First-launch default user | Basic Needs, Offers, Trades, proposals, profile, support | Pro, Business, ads, wallet, payouts |
+| Individual Pro | Future professional individual | Verification badge, profile tools, more media, Pro trade packages, analytics | Organization ownership, campaign budgets, KYB |
+| Business / Enterprise | Verified organization account | Brand profile, team members, sponsored Needs/Offers, library items, campaigns | Wallet, payouts, paid jobs, credits/tokens |
+| Ads | Placement/rendering layer | Sponsored slots, labels, frequency controls, provider SDKs later | Business identity, KYB, campaign budget source of truth |
+| Money Provider | Payment infrastructure | KYC/KYB, wallet, pay-ins, payouts, ledger, budgets | First-launch Business behavior |
+
+Product rule:
+
+```txt
+Business is an organization identity and reviewed-content system.
+Pro is an individual professional subscription.
+Ads are a placement layer.
+Money providers are financial infrastructure.
+```
+
+Do not collapse these into one feature.
+
+## Business profile model
+
+Use `BusinessProfile` as the organization record.
+
+Recommended profile types:
+
+```txt
+business
+agency
+brand
+enterprise
+```
+
+Recommended profile statuses:
+
+```txt
+draft
+pending_review
+verified
+restricted
+disabled
+rejected
+```
+
+The existing schema also contains `active`. Keep supporting it for compatibility, but future public behavior should prefer this safer interpretation:
+
+```txt
+draft:
+  created but not submitted
+
+pending_review:
+  waiting for admin review
+
+verified:
+  public Business identity is approved
+
+restricted:
+  visible only in limited/internal contexts or blocked from publishing
+
+disabled:
+  disabled by admin or owner action
+
+rejected:
+  review failed; not public
+```
+
+A Business profile should store at least:
+
+```txt
+owner user
+business type
+display name
+legal name
+handle
+website URL
+country
+preferred currency
+verification/review status
+reviewer
+review note
+reviewed timestamp
+verified timestamp
+```
+
+## Verification and KYB
+
+Business verification has two levels.
+
+### Level 1: Hellowhen business review
+
+Use this for non-money Business visibility.
+
+Required before public Business content:
+
+```txt
+owner is an individual 18+ Hellowhen account
+owner email is verified
+business display name is clear
+legal name is provided when available
+website or official public link is provided
+country is provided
+business type is selected
+admin review note is required
+admin reviewer and reviewedAt are stored
+```
+
+This review allows:
+
+```txt
+verified Business badge
+public Business profile later
+reviewed sponsored Needs/Offers later
+reviewed library templates later
+```
+
+It does not allow:
+
+```txt
+wallet
+campaign budgets
+credits/tokens/tickets/checks
+paid jobs
+payouts
+provider account production access
+```
+
+### Level 2: Provider KYB
+
+Use this only when money, budgets, payouts, or provider wallets are introduced.
+
+Provider KYB may use:
+
+```txt
+Airwallex later
+Stripe later
+another approved provider later
+```
+
+Provider KYB should be required before:
+
+```txt
+campaign budgets
+business wallet balances
+paid campaign opportunities
+voucher-like credits
+payout flows
+large spending limits
+```
+
+Product rule:
+
+```txt
+Hellowhen review can verify a public Business identity.
+Provider KYB is required for financial capabilities.
+```
+
+## Team and member roles
+
+Every Business team member must still be an individual Hellowhen account.
+
+Recommended roles:
+
+| Role | Meaning |
+| --- | --- |
+| owner | Full control over the Business profile, team, review submissions, and final responsibility |
+| admin | Manage Business content and team members, except owner transfer/destructive owner actions |
+| finance | Future-only budget, invoice, provider onboarding, and spending controls |
+| member | Draft content and participate in assigned workflows, but cannot publish or submit financial actions alone |
+
+Required future team flows before public Business launch:
+
+```txt
+invite member by email
+accept invite
+resend invite
+cancel invite
+remove member
+change member role
+leave business
+owner transfer, later only with sensitive-action reauth
+team audit log
+```
+
+Permission rule:
+
+```txt
+owner/admin can submit content for review
+member can draft content only
+finance has no special effect while money is disabled
+```
+
+## Sponsored Needs, Offers, and library items
+
+Business accounts should first create reviewed sponsored content, not normal personal trades.
+
+Recommended first Business content types:
+
+```txt
+Business Need
+Business Offer
+Business library template
+```
+
+Examples:
+
+```txt
+A verified agency needs landing page feedback.
+A verified brand offers a free creator briefing session.
+A verified partner publishes a starter library template users can clone.
+```
+
+Content flow:
+
+```txt
+Business creates draft
+Business owner/admin submits for review
+Admin reviews
+Admin approves or rejects
+Approved item becomes discoverable in allowed surfaces
+Individual user can clone, save, propose, or create a trade from it
+```
+
+Business-created content must always be labeled clearly:
+
+```txt
+Sponsored
+Business
+Verified brand
+By <Business display name>
+```
+
+Do not make sponsored Business content look identical to normal user content.
+
+### Library item behavior
+
+Business library templates should use the existing template model:
+
+```txt
+InventoryTemplate.sourceType = business | brand | partner
+InventoryTemplate.businessProfileId = <BusinessProfile id>
+```
+
+When an individual user clones a Business template:
+
+```txt
+created Need/Offer belongs to the user
+sourceTemplateId preserves template attribution
+Business does not automatically gain access to the user-owned clone
+```
+
+## Campaigns and jobs
+
+Do not launch full jobs first.
+
+Use safer product language:
+
+```txt
+campaign
+opportunity
+collaboration
+brief
+sponsored need
+sponsored offer
+```
+
+Avoid first:
+
+```txt
+job
+paid job
+salary
+contractor marketplace
+cash reward
+bounty
+commission
+voucher cash-out
+```
+
+Recommended campaign stages:
+
+### Stage 1: Sponsored Need / Offer
+
+One reviewed Business-created item appears in discovery.
+
+No money.
+
+### Stage 2: Campaign / opportunity
+
+A Business groups multiple reviewed items under one brief.
+
+Possible fields:
+
+```txt
+businessProfileId
+title
+brief
+description
+eligibility
+expected deliverables
+timeline
+number of spots
+linked Needs/Offers/templates
+review status
+```
+
+Still no money.
+
+### Stage 3: Paid campaign
+
+Only after provider KYB, legal/payment review, ledger, refunds, limits, and admin payout/budget tooling exist.
+
+## Business ads and placements
+
+Separate two concepts.
+
+### First-party sponsored Business placements
+
+These are promoted Hellowhen-native cards created by verified Business accounts and approved by admin.
+
+Possible future placements:
+
+```txt
+Trades feed deck
+Needs/Offers discovery surfaces
+Starter library surfaces
+Business profile page
+Campaign/opportunity list
+```
+
+Rules:
+
+```txt
+always label Sponsored
+never be the first card by default
+never hide the Business identity
+never use private proposal data for targeting
+never appear in private/sensitive flows
+```
+
+### External ad providers
+
+External ad providers such as AdSense or AdMob are separate from Business accounts.
+
+They must stay disabled until privacy/consent/store requirements are ready.
+
+Do not connect Business sponsored content to external ad provider SDKs in the first Business phase.
+
+## Disallowed placements
+
+Do not show Business sponsored content or ads in:
+
+```txt
+private proposal threads
+private chat
+proposal composer
+create Need form
+create Offer form
+create Trade form
+account security
+2FA
+password reset
+support ticket form before submit
+report flow
+admin pages
+wallet / payout screens
+```
+
+## Budget, credit, token, ticket, and check risk
+
+Business campaign budgets, credits, tokens, tickets, checks, coupons, perks, and vouchers are high-risk features.
+
+They may create requirements around:
+
+```txt
+stored value
+wallet balances
+advertising credits
+gift card or voucher rules
+refunds
+chargebacks
+tax/accounting treatment
+expiry rules
+consumer protection
+fraud controls
+provider approval
+KYB
+ledger reconciliation
+```
+
+Do not build these as simple app-only balances.
+
+Future rule:
+
+```txt
+Any Business budget or credit system must be owned by the Money Provider and Ledger roadmap, not by the Business profile roadmap alone.
+```
+
+Safe early substitute:
+
+```txt
+manual sponsored priority
+admin-approved placement
+manual start/end date
+manual internal notes
+```
+
+Unsafe first-launch items:
+
+```txt
+Business tops up credit
+campaign spends down balance
+tokens usable by users
+tickets/checks with value
+redeemable coupons
+user cash-out from Business campaign
+```
+
+## Admin review and moderation
+
+Before Business accounts become public, admin needs stronger controls.
+
+Minimum admin tools:
+
+```txt
+Business profile review queue
+verify / reject / restrict / disable Business profile
+mandatory admin note for each status action
+reviewer and reviewedAt stored
+Business action audit log
+view owner and members
+view linked Needs/Offers/Trades/templates
+review Business-created content
+approve/reject/hide/restore sponsored content
+emergency disable all content from one Business profile
+reports linked to Business profile/content
+support escalation from Business content
+```
+
+Business admin actions should be auditable:
+
+```txt
+who acted
+what action happened
+previous status
+next status
+target type
+target id
+reason/note
+timestamp
+```
+
+## First-launch hidden rules
+
+Keep Business hidden for the first public launch.
+
+Required defaults:
+
+```txt
+BUSINESS_ACCOUNTS_VISIBLE=false
+NEXT_PUBLIC_BUSINESS_ACCOUNTS_VISIBLE=false
+EXPO_PUBLIC_BUSINESS_ACCOUNTS_VISIBLE=false
+```
+
+Also keep related future systems hidden:
+
+```txt
+ADS_ENABLED=false
+WEB_ADS_ENABLED=false
+MOBILE_ADS_ENABLED=false
+ADS_PROVIDER=none
+
+SUBSCRIPTIONS_ENABLED=false
+PRO_ACCOUNTS_ENABLED=false
+PRO_ACCOUNTS_VISIBLE=false
+PRO_TRIALS_ENABLED=false
+PRO_TRADE_PACKAGES_ENABLED=false
+
+MONEY_PROVIDER=none
+MONEY_PROVIDER_ACCOUNT_CREATION_ENABLED=false
+MONEY_PROVIDER_WALLET_SYNC_ENABLED=false
+MONEY_PROVIDER_PAYINS_ENABLED=false
+MONEY_PROVIDER_TRADE_MONEY_ENABLED=false
+MONEY_PROVIDER_PAYOUTS_ENABLED=false
+MONEY_PROVIDER_WEBHOOKS_ENABLED=false
+STRIPE_CONNECT_ENABLED=false
+AIRWALLEX_ENABLED=false
+AIRWALLEX_CONNECTED_ACCOUNTS_ENABLED=false
+
+AI_ENABLED=false
+```
+
+Do not show:
+
+```txt
+Business tab
+Business onboarding
+Business profile creation
+verified brand badge
+sponsored feed cards
+campaigns/jobs
+Business budgets
+credits/tokens/tickets/checks
+wallet/payout UI
+Stripe/Airwallex Business onboarding
+```
+
+## Recommended patch sequence
+
+### Patch B2 — Business flags and guard cleanup
+
+Add clearer separate flags:
+
+```txt
+BUSINESS_ACCOUNTS_ENABLED=false
+BUSINESS_ACCOUNTS_VISIBLE=false
+BUSINESS_SPONSORED_CONTENT_ENABLED=false
+BUSINESS_CAMPAIGNS_ENABLED=false
+```
+
+Goal:
+
+```txt
+visible controls public exposure
+enabled controls internal route/API access
+sponsored content and campaigns have separate switches
+```
+
+### Patch B3 — Admin Business review hardening
+
+Add:
+
+```txt
+mandatory review notes
+Business action audit log
+reviewer/timestamp consistency
+admin filters by status/type/country
+emergency disable action
+```
+
+### Patch B4 — Team/member foundation
+
+Add:
+
+```txt
+member invites
+accept/cancel invite
+role changes
+remove member
+owner/admin/member permission helpers
+team audit events
+```
+
+No sponsored content yet.
+
+### Patch B5 — Business-owned library templates
+
+Use existing template fields.
+
+Add:
+
+```txt
+Business draft template creation
+submit template for review
+admin approve/reject
+approved template appears in starter/library surfaces only when flags allow it
+clone keeps source attribution
+```
+
+### Patch B6 — Business-owned Needs/Offers
+
+Wire Business ownership into create/update flows behind flags.
+
+Rules:
+
+```txt
+owner/admin can create and submit
+member can draft
+admin review required before public discovery
+Business attribution is always visible
+```
+
+### Patch B7 — First-party sponsored placement model
+
+Add metadata for native sponsored placement:
+
+```txt
+placement
+priority
+label
+startsAt
+endsAt
+review status
+frequency cap later
+```
+
+No external ad SDKs.
+
+### Patch B8 — Campaign/opportunity skeleton
+
+Add hidden campaign models and APIs.
+
+No money.
+
+Use:
+
+```txt
+campaign
+opportunity
+collaboration
+brief
+```
+
+Avoid paid job language.
+
+### Patch B9 — Provider-backed Business budget sandbox
+
+Only after legal/payment/provider review.
+
+Requires:
+
+```txt
+Airwallex or Stripe KYB
+Business provider account
+ledger entries
+budget limits
+refund rules
+admin review
+webhooks
+reconciliation
+```
+
+## Implementation principle
+
+Build Business in this order:
+
+```txt
+identity
+review
+team
+reviewed content
+sponsored placement
+campaigns
+provider-backed budgets
+```
+
+Do not begin with money.
+
+Do not reveal Business in the first launch.
